  <a href="#1" id="1">
   The McMartin Pre-school molestation case was the longest criminal trial in U.S. history.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   12, 1983: Judy Johnson makes a phone call to Manhattan Beach Police Department and tells Detective Jane Hoag that she believes her 2-year-old son was molested by Raymond Buckey at the McMartin Pre-School.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   17, 1988: The judge dismisses eight molestation counts against Buckey and his mother.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   They now face a combined 65 counts of molestation and conspiracy involving 11 former McMartin pupils.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   _Feb. The judge declares a mistrial on 13 other counts _ 12 against Buckey and one against both Buckey and his mother.
  </a>
